news.title: Infopark phase III aims to attract global investors in Kerala Global Summit
news.para: To present the project at the summit, the govt has begun finalizing the components and concept designs of the multi-crore township. The Greater Cochin Development Authority (GCDA) has identified three potential land parcels, each 300 acres, in the Kizhakkambalam and Kunnathunadu areas

news.title: NDMC budget 2025-26: No hike in property tax, focuses on infra and green initiatives
news.para: Presenting his first budget after taking charge last month, NDMC chairman Keshav Chandra announced no increase in property tax for the new fiscal.

news.title: Ranchi civic body cracks down on property tax defaulters
news.para: RMC commissioner Sandeep Singh said the focus is on properties with substantial outstanding tax payments and regulatory violations. The revenue generated from the campaign would support urban development, he said.

news.title: Pune metro line three likely to be ready by April 2025
news.para: The flyover work was initially stated to be completed by Nov this year. It was then pushed to Dec. The delay will impact the opening of the entire 23-km Metro corridor from Maan to Shivajinagar.

news.title: Lucknow development body addresses grievances on land disputes and housing issues
news.para: ​​Ali alleged someone impersonated him to get the registry transferred in his name and that despite approaching police and LDA, no action was taken. Divisional commissioner Roshan Jacob assured the issue would be addressed.

news.title: Lucknow: ED attaches Rs 3.91 crore assets in PMLA case against Sai Construction and Builders
news.para: The ED initiated an investigation based on an FIR registered by CBI, Ghaziabad under various sections of IPC, 1860 and the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988, against M/s Sai Construction and Builders, Ghaziabad, its partners and others for alleged loan fraud.

news.title: BMC officials can’t be silent spectators to illegalities: Bombay HC
news.para: The HC directed demolition of three structures in two weeks and action against concerned civic officials who patently failed to act despite non-compliance of a 30-year-old undertaking by their late owner to raze them herself.

news.title: Uttarakhand cabinet eases norms under affordable housing scheme
news.para: The carpet area of EWS homes would be 30sqm and the amount charged from the beneficiaries would be Rs 9 lakh for one unit. Similarly, the criteria for lower income group (LIG) and lower middle income groups (LMIG) has also been defined.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Builders in Crossings Republik seek five years to address pending civic works
news.para: The consortium made a presentation to the principal secretary of housing and urban planning, seeking the same.

news.title: Hyderabad: ED files complaint against Sahiti Infratec and its MD under PMLA
news.para: ED initiated its probe based on an FIR filed by Telangana police against SIVIPL, B Lakshminarayana, and others for promoting a pre-launch offer for a world-class residential gated community.

news.title: Magicbricks acquires majority stake in PropViz
news.para: In a statement on Thursday, Magicbricks said this strategic acquisition underscores its mission to provide best-in-class technology for redefining real estate interactions and creating new benchmarks in customer engagement.

news.title: Haryana RERA orders NBCC to pay Rs 30,000 to Green View buyers till handover of flats
news.para: The decision came after two allottees, Saurabh Mehta and Jai Prakash Mehta, had filed a complaint with the regulatory body following structural audits conducted by IIT-Roorkee and the Central Building Research Institute (CBRI) found the Green View Society project ‘unsafe' for living.

news.title: ED facilitates refund for two victims of Shine City Infra projects
news.para: Judge Rahul Prakash of the Special Court directed the ED to refund Rs 7.61 lakh to Husna Bano and Rs 4 lakh to Neeta Verma, both of whom were duped by the company.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body to introduce GRAP against pollution
news.para: At present, GRAP I is in force considering the city's air quality index (AQI) is between 101 and 300 (moderate to poor). That means the civic body will have to focus on controlling road dust, restricting illegal waste dumping, and improving traffic management.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body invites private firms to draft Harnandipuram layout
news.para: Three companies have made presentations, and these will be followed by the opening of financial bids, officials said.

news.title: NGT directs Haryana govt to act against illegal mining in Faridabad's Anangpur forest
news.para: The directive follows a report from the joint committee set up by the tribunal, highlighting unauthorised activities on land classified as forest under the Forest (Conservation) Act, 1980.

news.title: UK announces planning overhaul to build 1.5 million homes in five years
news.para: The housebuilding target was one of six measurable "milestones" announced by Prime Minister Keir Starmer a week ago, as he pledged to revamp a planning system he described as having a "chokehold" on growth.

news.title: Lucknow development body simplifies construction unsealing process
news.para: LDA vice-chairman Prathmesh Kumar issued new directives to streamline the procedure, prioritising public convenience.

news.title: NCLAT appoints NBCC as PMC for completion of 16 Supertech projects
news.para: "The NBCC shall start process of award of work as per Condition-IV, prior to March 31, 2025 and complete the award of contract within one month thereafter and construction shall commence with effect from May 01, 2025," said NCLAT in its order.

news.title: Ina Invest and Cham Group near merger, shareholder vote in March 2025
news.para: If negotiations are successful, the merger will be submitted to both companies' shareholders for approval at their annual general meetings on March 31, 2025, Ina said in a statement.
